				<wikidot:authorName>Prototype_Toaster</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3512728</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>My apologies for the vague feedback in chat.</p> <p>I feel that this really comes down to the bug table you have in the middle. Some people may find them funny however I could barely crack a smile at some of them.</p> <p>The bug spectacle to me was the Finland joke at the end. Not the War &amp; Peace seized except you have there but the researcher self adding the meta tag is what made me laugh.</p> <p>I also feel that something leading to the downvotes from users here is the use of the 🅱️eter classification. Now I've seen this joke a lot in the satellite fandom but on site this can cause a lot of people to downvote to it referencing an actual meme. Referencing actual memes is not the best idea for a -J.</p> <p>I am upvoting for the Finland part, but I am teetering on a novote</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
